OL,3,CPope Francis would have felt 'at home'
OL,4,Cin North West
OL,6,FProfessor Anna Rowlands, from
OL,7,FManchester, previously spent two years
OL,8,Fseconded to the Vatican during his
OL,9,Fpapacy, happened to be in the Italian
OL,10,Fcapital for Easter.
OL,12,FRecalling sharing a football joke with
OL,13,Fthe pontiff, she said the religious
OL,14,Fleader had roared with laughter when
OL,15,Fshe told him she was a Manchester
OL,16,FUnited fan the first time they spoke
OL,17,Fat length.
OL,19,FShe said his natural approach was to
OL,20,F"find a point of human connection"
OL,21,Fwith whoever he was speaking to.
