OL,6,FProf Rowlands said: "He wanted to know
OL,7,Fwhat football team I supported, and I
OL,8,Fsaid that I was from Manchester, and
OL,9,Fso I was a genuine, bona fide
OL,10,FMancunian, Manchester United fan by
OL,11,Forigin, to which he just sort of
OL,12,Froared laughing and turned to his aide
OL,13,Fand said, 'you see, she must have a
OL,14,Fsense of humour'.
OL,16,F"That was the first extended
OL,17,Fconversation I'd ever had with him.
OL,18,FSo, his nature was to tease you
OL,19,Fslightly and to be good-humoured, and
OL,20,Ffind a point of human connection with
OL,21,Fyou."
