OL,3,CPope Francis would have felt 'at home'
OL,4,Cin North West
OL,6,F"It wasn't as if you were meeting the
OL,7,FPope at all, you could be meeting the
OL,8,Flocal parish priest, that sort of
OL,9,Fthing, and always always with a smile."
OL,11,FThe Right Reverend Arnold said he
OL,12,Fhoped whoever would succeed Pope
OL,13,FFrancis would "follow up with the same
OL,14,Fteachings", "looking always to the
OL,15,Fdignity of everybody".
OL,17,F"I think that we will recognise
OL,18,Fincreasingly the importance of what he
OL,19,Fhad to say to us," he added, speaking
OL,20,Fon his teachings.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/14
